  <h1 class="gd-h1">What to Pack for Heliskiing</h1>
  <p class="gd-byline" style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:12.5px;letter-spacing:.05em;color:var(--blue-soft);opacity:.9;margin:16px 0 0">By <a href="/about" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px">Vegard Knudsen</a> · Founder, Heliski Travel · Updated 13 Jun 2026</p>
  <p class="gd-lede">You have booked, or nearly booked, the trip of a lifetime. Now the only question left is what goes in the bag. This is the definitive gear and packing checklist for a spring heliski trip, built around our <a href="/packages">packages</a> with Viking Heliskiing in <a href="/iceland">Iceland</a> so you arrive ready to ski from your very first lift-off.</p>
